spanGrp.span: There are no mother nor father
charapa ru cavangpa akhe he to lulām ṭojenu̠
An orhpan and a rich man became friends.
As they went to set traps,
carapahe tuwng doltiha chakhọ atāng thinu̠
the orphan set a deer trap on the ground.
chavangpa he tuwng vāngkāl len pahatāng thinu̠
The rich boy set a bird trap in the height.
vajọngha tuwng iveel vachaka ve dọnāte
The next day they said "Let's go visit (check the traps)"
charapa he to te jọng tuwng chọọso dọnite vapoose to hnum tiiso
The orphan, if he went, his clothes would get wet.
and afterwards he would have nothing (to wear).
dọnate nibe oh, atunghe ani saso avape kaning ve"
He said "As for me, I will come later, when the sun rises up"
dolti tuwng charapa atāng thung tuwng chakhọ to aminnu̠
In the orhpan's trap on the ground there was a trapped deer.
su̠w hlonu̠ le vāngkālha hang... hang thu̠nu̠
He took it out and went up with it.
vāngkāl len pahatāng charee thung tuwng chakhọ to vāpa- khe- vāpakhe leeolova
Up there he hung the deer openly inside the small bird trap.
My friendǃ There was nothing caught in our traps.
Atung athu̠wn vakhu̠ chaka no vadọva
Later in the noon he said "Let's go againǃ"
He dropped by after the food.
chakhọ he to vāngkāl lenha atho lelocha
that deer is hanging in the height
Kahloǃ Chakhọ akheh to datung vāngkālha amin hlonaka?
My friendǃ How would a deer be trapped in the height?
ni kātāng thung ki su̠w tinu̠ āpemin va
You took it out from my trap and trpped it (in yours).
Ma eǃ Ni kātāng thung rara amin va dọnu̠
No, he said, it was caught inside my trap.
ire vaje. Vāree nā jete ningtho ju̠wng tuwng va vakā vaje
They quarreled and put a case to the king.
Ningtho to aku̠va dọsing sung dọ nibe, chavangpato vapato ningtho va
When we say who was a king, the rich man -his father is the king.
Vapa ku̠wng tuwng atāng damoto vato kājenu̠ vāre nājete
They put a case about the trap to his father and argued about it.
Vapahin tuwng vajọọl iṭo pachāng macha
His father could not settle the dispute.
"Go down and call the wise manǃ"
Ama vajọọl he nāṭo pe vahinso
He will settle the case for us.
Ningtho ahangso vajọọl kāṭo pe vaso vadọmang ve dọnu̠
The king tells you to come and settle a case.
"Da vajọọl kaṭo hrang va?" vadọ thung tuwng
He said "What case should I settle?"
"A deer was caught inside a bird trap".
There is a dispute about it."
Hangdee manu̠, tanā hatute atung hatute vahang nāte
He did not go for a very long time. Then he went very slowly.
"Daki ihang thang mavati? Datung ito doo vati?"
Why didn't you come for a very long time? Why are yoo so late?"
Earlier, I was about to go
But when I was just about to leave
hakang nāte hlam thung tuwng, dahva
as I was going up, what's thatǃ
Abuwng dọnu̠ thingchu akheto khang chuw ichuva amato
there was a tree full of fruits
many tiny fish, fish of that kind
ngatara ṭọ hin tuwng vachā nājete isu nunge pānu̠
As the fish were eating (the fruits, it was very beautiful to look at.
kasu jānāte khang nunge nungenu̠ ito nool vaning veveǃ
I was just looking at it, and it was so nice, so I am very late.
Don't just try to fool meǃ
Ngatara ṭọ adọ hlān chee tuwng
Datung vāngkālha hangkalso abuwngchu to chanaka?
How would they climb up and eat fruits?
Ningtho, nangso chakhọ to datung vāngkālha hangkalso
King, you too, how would a deer climb a tree
vāngkal len abuwng- abuwngchu to chanaka?
vapalung to nunge ṭọọ khu̠ manu̠
Go down and call the wise manǃ
"Kachahmu patal e, sankoom ahang phen vaso" vadọ khu̠va
My bull, let him come and milk itǃ"
Amāputhi ohǃ Ningtho @ atatuwng vadamang veǃ
The wise manǃ The king said like thatǃ
I will come up. Go away - he said
He stayed for long time again and then again went up.
Daki ihang thang mavati" vadọ nā khu̠ nāte
Why didn't you come for a long time", (the king) asked again.
"Ahang kaning" kadọ thung ra tuwng ne
Just in the moment I said "I'll go up (to the king)"
kapa- kapa chara (i)ṭho nahrang ki pachānu̠
my dad felt the labour of child delivery.
Ama kāsol thu̠ lii khu̠ vaǃ"
I stayed for a long time helping him.
"Simpa akheh tuwng datung chara ṭho naka?"
"How a man would give birth to a child?"
"Tute nangte achahmu patal datung sankoom phen kaning?"
"So how can I milk the bull of yours?"
Juwl khu̠cha. Vajọngha tuwng ṭum kheh khu̠
He lost again. The enxt morning once again
he wasn't satisfied and went again:
go and let the wise man come up here."
hru̠hrol dọnite ataheng hru̠ nana hrol rang hru̠hrol lue
A thread that we spin like that
let him spin ashes that way, and to bring it here, to come here
If he does not bring it here
he will be killed with a golden knife."
Vapalung he khang jā jā nu̠
He was just sitting at the night.
He was just sitting by the fire.
vabool hru̠moong he to kānu̠ iam lelāva
a piece of a head-basket rope remained after burning.
As he touched it, it became ashes.
lihlo hru̠ to buthi to linu̠ pahol rangnu̠
He took out a thread, an old cloth, and spinned it properly.
He did like that again and again.
iṭha tangna dọrangnu̠ amathal tuwng te
He did it well and then
vajọngha tuwng atatuwng pakān thung hangsin lelanu̠ ahangcha
the enxt morning he went up (to the king̠ carrying it on a plate.
He touched it and it became ashes.
Datung ahrorva amahe te" vadọ hloval
How did you spin it?" he asked in turn.
Vathung he to khang sa sanu̠
"Atung dacha kāpachāng dodo va chaǃ" dọnu̠
"How come he defeated me nowǃ" he said.
vamine hin to mi thum mi pali ju̠sọ jenu̠
He sent his three or four servants.
"Ju̠hinnu̠ amāputhi e vain thung ae pe lukhinǃ"
"Go down, this wise man - shit all over his houseǃ"
Ningtho "vain thung ae lukhin" kādọmang veǃ
The king tells us "Shit all over his houseǃ"
To shit - go ahead and shitǃ
"drop" akheh pe- ichar poso hro maning noǃ" vadọmang
I don't agree for a single drop leakingǃ"
Dolthu hin ti sung peesunma pachāng na mahinti?"
As you defecate, how wouldn't you urinate?"
So the wise man won again.
